text: Maung Maung Swe ( , born 23 May 1971) is a Burmese politician who currently serves as an Amyotha Hluttaw MP for Mandalay Region No. 9 Constituency. He is a member of National League for Democracy. ==Early life and education== He was born on 23 May 1971 in Rakhine State, Burma (Myanmar). He graduated with B.A in History from Dagon University. ==Political career== He is a member of the National League for Democracy. In the Myanmar general election, 2015, he was elected as an Amyotha Hluttaw MP and elected representative from Mandalay Region № 9 parliamentary constituency. ==References== Category:National League for Democracy politicians Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:People from Rakhine State
title: Maung Maung Swe
